			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>The Company</strong><br />
Samasource is an award-winning social enterprise with a huge vision - to pioneer a model for internet-based work that can move millions of people out of poverty. Samasource combines the fast-paced, results-driven culture of a tech start-up with the impact and social mission of a non-profit. We like to move quickly and get things done - if you join us, you will be part of a dynamic team that is passionate about making an impact.</p>
<p>
Samasource was founded in 2008 and is supported by major corporate and philanthropic funders including MasterCard, Google, eBay, Cisco, Rockefeller, Ford and the State Department. Headquartered in San Francisco&rsquo;s Mission District, Samasource has 30+ employees and gives work to thousands of people worldwide.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>The Program</strong><br />
The Associate Program offers a rare opportunity to play a major role in expanding Samasource&rsquo;s mission of bringing dignified computer-based work to people living in poverty while also providing a unique insider experience. We give candidates a chance to integrate across our organization and observe firsthand the effect of our work. We don&rsquo;t accept the world for what it is, but instead design solutions to help mold it into what we think it could be. We want to hear from individuals with a unique perspective and a desire to make an immediate impact.</p>
<p>
Associates are expected to commit to a minimum of 10 weeks of full-time work, usually based in our San Francisco office, and will be paid&nbsp; for participating in our program. Specific tasks will be assigned depending on your interest and background. Make&nbsp; sure to tell us your area of expertise and why you think that you would make a great fit.</p>
<p>
<u>Application deadlines:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>May 3, 2013</strong> for Summer Associate Program (start date June 17, 2013)</li>
<li>
<strong>July 26, 2013</strong> for Fall Associate Program (start date September 2, 2013)</li>
</ul>
<p>
Past participants have found the Associate Program to be a rewarding experience in the field of international development and have made lasting connections with professionals motivated by nonprofit work. If you are looking to play a key role in connecting marginalized people with truly life-changing work opportunities, then we are your company.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Entering final year of degree program with strong academic record or a recent graduate&nbsp; with a BA or BS&nbsp; from a top-tier university.</li>
<li>
Comfort with a fast-paced, always-on, highly ambiguous start-up environment</li>
<li>
Prior experience working in a high-growth or start-up technology or business services company a plus</li>
<li>
Proven track record with high standards of professionalism</li>
<li>
Exceptional interpersonal skills</li>
<li>
Creative, resourceful, detail-oriented, highly organized</li>
<li>
Proficiency in MS Office, with experience working in a Mac environment&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>
<li>
Passionate about our mission to alleviate poverty by connecting people to digital work</li>
<li>
Must be eligible to work in the U.S. and able to commute to the San Francisco office for the duration of the internship</li>
</ul>
