			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Samahope:</strong><br />
Samahope harnesses the power of the internet to fund critical medical treatments for those who cannot afford them. We are revolutionizing the way global health is funded.</p>
<p>
Sama means &ldquo;equal&rdquo; in Sanskrit and reflects our desire to provide equal access to basic medical care to low-income patients. Samahope partners with local charity hospitals and global health organizations with a track record of excellent care and fiscal discipline. These partners provide care for the world&rsquo;s poorest, performing high-impact and low-cost surgeries and other life-saving interventions.</p>
<p>
Samahope&rsquo;s efforts to date have been featured in FastCompany, TechCrunch, the DailyBeast, SF Chronicle and others. Samahope is a sister organization to Samasource, an award-winning technology social enterprise that provides dignified, internet-based work to people living in poverty.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Team:</strong><br />
We are a small but hardcore startup, building on the momentum achieved so far. We are each driven by the power the web can have to help save lives of women and children across the world. Candidates will have an opportunity to shape and contribute meaningfully to getting Samahope off the ground. We&rsquo;ve got a big vision - to fund 1 Million patients in need - and need the best and brightest to help us achieve it. We like to move fast and get things done.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Job:</strong><br />
We are looking for a passionate Technical Lead to help build Samahope, our life-changing medical treatment crowdfunding site. This technical powerhouse will work on critical elements of the online platform. This person will get to put his/her stellar developer skills to work to change the lives of women and children globally. She/he will also have the opportunity to get involved across general strategy and operations (e.g., donor experience), to help ensure Samahope&rsquo;s success.</p>
<p>
<strong>In this role, you are:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
a founding partner, ready to advocate for and make decisions that will allow Samahope to thrive</li>
<li>
data driven, you track everything that happens on your applications, and know performance of features and functionality before anyone else</li>
<li>
a careful product thinker, able to translate user requirements into elegant features&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
the last line of defense, when the unexpected scaling challenge hits, you&rsquo;ve jumped on the production servers and stabilized the app</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Build new features and interfaces for Samahope</li>
<li>
Redefine and iterate on website interfaces to make the donor experience seamless and enjoyable</li>
<li>
Work with the team to continuously improve the presentation and mining of important metrics</li>
<li>
Enhance global partner interfaces, streamlining medical partner delivery of required treatment information and updates</li>
<li>
Translate good design to web work</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
